    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT - 9600, 9700, 9800 - ASSEMBLE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="1">
            <title>TILT MECHANISM</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the positioning pin in the bracket in the proper orientation. Assemble the tilt
                    cam, the three (3) spring washers and the special washer on the positioning pin (
                    <hotlnk document="s05010t_8.xml" xrefid="f0501018">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the tilt lever on the positioning pin and insert the roll pins in the tilt lever
                    and the tilt cam (
                    <hotlnk document="s05010t_8.xml" xrefid="f0501017">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Compress the tilt lever tension spring and insert the retaining ring (
                    <hotlnk document="s05010t_8.xml" xrefid="f0501016">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble the cone, spring washer, special washer and retaining nut on the positioning
                    pin (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0501019">Figure 19</hotlnk>). With a box end wrench tighten the retaining nut one
                    quarter (1/4) turn. Using two wrenches, install and tighten the locking nut (
                    <hotlnk document="s05010t_8.xml" xrefid="f0501015">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501019" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0501019" filename="../figg05/g0501019.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Tilt Lever Retaining Components</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CONE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SPRING WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SPECIAL WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. RETAINING NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. LOCKING NUT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
